history.content:
I would suggest dropping one of the other 2 first actually. Both 170 and 126 are a lot of work, and I don't think you will get the maximum benefit of the classes if taken together. Especially considering how important 170 is.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

If you're OK with a lot of work with heavy psets, but don't want a time conflict: drop 188.

If you're OK with a time conflict but prefer not to deal with a lot of work with heavy psets: drop 126 (take this in Spring).

General advice is to take 170 ASAP for pretty much any EECS/CS major so prioritize 170.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

As someone who has taken 170 and 126 concurrently (in fact, those were the only technicals for the semester), I'd say take both only if you have a really good reason to do so. Otherwise, I advise to come up with a different combo. 170 and 126 are equally heavy. 170 is more important in general, more fun and more organized. 126 is messier and the difficulty comes from that fact, in my opinion. I took it for 189 (haven't taken 189 yet though).
